---
import Feature from '../../layouts/Feature.astro';
---

<Feature
  title="MULTI-WINDOW"
  subtitle="Multiple windows, per-window DPI, cross-window tab movement."
>
  <div class="roadmap-note">
    <strong>Window architecture is in transition.</strong> Today, all windows live in one process and share a single GPU device. The next milestone moves to a process-per-window model with the mux daemon coordinating shared state. Cross-window tab movement is preserved across the transition.
  </div>

  <h2>Cross-Window Tab Movement</h2>
  <p>Drag tabs between windows or use a keyboard shortcut to move a tab to a new window. The shell session, scrollback, and layout travel with the tab through the mux layer.</p>

  <div class="screenshot-placeholder" role="img" aria-label="Screenshot of multiple ori-term windows with tabs being dragged between them">
    <span>[ SCREENSHOT COMING SOON ]</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Per-Window DPI</h2>
  <p>Each window tracks its own display scale factor. Moving a window from a standard-DPI monitor to a HiDPI display triggers an immediate rescale — fonts, chrome, and terminal content stay sharp without manual intervention.</p>

  <h2>Aero Snap</h2>
  <p>Full Windows Aero Snap support across all windows. Drag to screen edges to snap left, right, or maximize. Each window snaps independently.</p>

  <h2>ConPTY-Safe Shutdown</h2>
  <p>On Windows, ori-term performs clean process cleanup when closing windows. ConPTY handles are released so child processes terminate gracefully and no orphaned shells leak.</p>
</Feature>

<style>
  .roadmap-note {
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .roadmap-note strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .screenshot-placeholder {
    border: var(--border-weight) solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-raised);
    padding: 120px 24px;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
</style>
